Heat oil in medium skillet to medium-high. Wash hands. Add chicken, cook 5 to 7 minutes or until light brown; season with salt and pepper, if desired. Add garlic; cook briefly. Stir in rice and chicken broth. Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is done (internal temp 170 degrees F). Remove from heat; stir in Parmesan cheese and peas. Cover and let stand 5 minutes before serving.